com.wm.xmldata

Class XmlDataTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wm.xmldata.XmlDataTag
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    XmlDataAttributeTag, XmlDataContentTag, XmlDataTypeTag

    public class XmlDataTag
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This iNs the base construction class for all XmlData tags. This class maintains the three portions on an XmlData as three distinct components: the ncName, the namespace, and the particle-id. The various methods of the XmlData implementations expect instances of the various subclass of this class. The methods do not generally accept simple Strings as tags. The choice of subclass depends on the context usage. There are subclasses for XmlDataElementTag, XmlDataAttributeTag, XmlDataGroupTag, XmlDataSubstitutionTag and XmlDataIteratorTag.

      • createInstanceFromFullName

        public static XmlDataTag createInstanceFromFullName(java.lang.String name,
                                                    boolean elementDefault,
                                                    XmlNamespaceMap nsDecls)
        Creates the appropriate XmlDataTag object from a literal tag String. It returns an instance of the appropriate subclass such as an XmlDataElementTag or an XmlDataGroupTag object, etc.
        Parameters:
        name - the full name of the tag. For example, "*group" or "{2}substitution-name#target", etc. When no particle id is specified for a tag that requires one, for example, *any, it defaults to {1}.
        elementDefault - specifies how to treat tags that do not start with the { character and also are not one the special tags such as *group or *instance. When false, it is treated as an attribute tag; when true it is treated as an element tag
        nsDecls - the namespace declarations
        Returns:
        an instance of XmlDataTag or one its subclasses

      • getFullName

        public java.lang.String getFullName()
        Creates the String representation of an XMlDataTag from its three components in the {particleId}ncName#namespace. For example, the third particle instance of a tag with ncName "sister" and namespace "family" is {3}sister#family. This is the name as it would appear in the pipeline and does not include an index or a indirect-qualifier
        Returns:
        The full name of this tag

      • getPathName

        public java.lang.String getPathName()
        Returns the tag in path-name format. The path-name is the full-name which include particle-id, ncName, and namespace as well as additional properties used by XmlDataMap or XmlDataCopy. The additional properties are index and indirect-qualifier. Qualified names are returned in the form ncName#namespace. Index (if defined) is represented as [index] and indirect-qualifiers is defined re represented as {consent-tag}. If the namespace uses the path characters '[', ']', or '/', those characters are %-encoded using %2F for /, %5B for [, %5D for ], and %25 for %.
        Returns:
        a String representation of the path-name

      • getPathName

        public java.lang.String getPathName(XmlNamespaceMap nsDecls)
        Returns the tag in path-name form using namespace prefixes. The path-name is the full name with additional properties as it is used by XmlDataMap or XmlDataCopy. Qualified names are returned in the form prefix:ncName. The prefix is defined by the nsDecls argument
        Parameters:
        nsDecls - the namespace declarations used to present names in prefixed form.
        Returns:
        the String representation as used in a path.

      • getPathName

        public java.lang.String getPathName(java.lang.String nsPairs)
        Return the tag in path-name form using namespace prefixes. The path-name is the full name with additional properties as it is used by XmlDataMap or XmlDataCopy. The prefix definitions are expressed as a String of blank-delimited prefix/URI pairs rather than an XmlNamespaceMap.
        Parameters:
        nsPairs - prefix/URI pairs
        Returns:
        the tag in path-name form.
